HOW TO FIX STUFF:

File permission errors:
  1. Add yourself to the group lonewoman on linux (sudo adduser USERNAME lonewoman)
  2. chown -R tencke:lonewoman /home/tencke

Citation issues:
  1. Check spread sheet first. Make sure you are looking at column actually being used during sync.
  2. If not a spreadsheet issue formatting is done in two different places mention in file descriptions above.

Sync issues:
  1. The sync tool code is in the LonewomanSync folder. I got a little sloppy with the code but it all is there
  and most likely won't need to be touched. Also it is written in JAVA and compiled to a jar that lives
  in lonewoman_content. Can be run using 
  (java -jar /home/tencke/public_html/lonewoman_content/LonewomanSync.jar force /home/tencke/public_html/lonewoman_content/config.json)

Internal Server Error:
  1. Could mean anything: email tylerencke.root@gmail.com and I can forward any errors to you.
  2. You can also just add your email to the settings.py and errors will be sent to you also.

Email issues:
  1. Check that the email is configured correctly in settings.py.
  I.E. the password is correct, etc.

Issues with one liners not showing up:
  1. Most likely it is N/A'd or the stylesheets is not making it a link.
  2. Check to make sure it is syncing correctly

Oneliners showing when not supposed to:
  1. Run the sync tool and check again.
  2. Still showing, make sure it is the correct key.
  3. Make sure it is N/A in the description
  4. If here you'll have to do some figuring out.


